Course in contract law comprise general principles of contract law, conclusion of contracts, content and performance of contracts, non-performance and remedies, termination of contracts, securities, change of parties. Special contracts as sale, lease, credit, deposit, and services will be covered.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To know and understand the main concepts of contract law, use the knowledges in drafting contracts and solving simple contractual disputes on basic level, understand the main features of special contracts.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Student should know and understand the main concepts of contract law, be able to use the knowledges in drafting contracts, know the main prinsiples of solving contractual disputes, understand the main features of special contracts.
